{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This article describes how KeyboardKit Pro can identify and use the host application."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit lets you get the bundle ID of the host application that is using the keyboard. This may be of interest for many reasons, e.g. to vary the style or functionality of the keyboard based on the currently active app."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"👑 "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" unlocks an additional "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardHostApplication"},{"text":" type that defines many common apps and makes it easier to identify and navigate to specific apps. This lets you open the main app to perform a task, then return to the keyboard.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Host Application Bundle Identifier","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Host-Application-Bundle-Identifier"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" has a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/hostApplicationBundleId"},{"type":"text","text":" property that resolves the bundle ID of the app that is currently using the keyboard."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The controller will automatically sync this property to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardContext","isActive":true},{"text":"’s au